ptrs-gesher
===========

Forked from `jmwample/ptrs` (https://github.com/jmwample/ptrs),
dual-licensed under MIT OR Apache-2.0. Substantial portions of the
following crates originate from that upstream:

  - crates/core   (formerly: crates/ptrs)
  - crates/obfs4  (formerly: crates/obfs4)
  - crates/lyrebird (formerly: crates/lyrebird; refactored to expose a
    library API alongside the binary, and dispatching to the new
    `webtunnel` transport by name)

Original copyright: Jack Wampler <jack.wampler@colorado.edu>.

The following are new in this fork (no upstream equivalent):

  - crates/webtunnel       — TLS + HTTP/1.1 Upgrade transport.
  - crates/bridge-line     — `Bridge` directive parser.
  - crates/ptrs-gesher     — umbrella crate.

The fork's working name "gesher" (גשר, Hebrew "bridge") refers both
to the cryptographic-bridges domain and to the fork relationship with
the upstream project.
